    using System;
    using System.IO;
    using System.Runtime.Serialization.Formatters.Binary;

    class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            var input = new[]
            {
                new DateTime(2018, 11, 13, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Local),
                new DateTime(2018, 11, 13, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Unspecified),
                new DateTime(2018, 11, 13, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Utc)
            };

            var formatter = new BinaryFormatter();
            using (var stream = new MemoryStream())
            {
                formatter.Serialize(stream, input);

                stream.Seek(0, SeekOrigin.Begin);

                var output = (DateTime[])formatter.Deserialize(stream);

                // Output:
                // NetFramework (4.7):  Local, Unspecified, Utc
                // CoreApp (2.1):       Unspecified, Unspecified, Unspecified

                Console.WriteLine($"{output[0].Kind}, {output[1].Kind}, {output[2].Kind}");
            }

            Console.ReadKey();
        }
    }

## Problem

When sending mail using the asynchronous method (`SendAsync`, `SendMailAsync`), set `DeliveryFormat` `=` `SmtpDeliveryFormat.SevenBit`，If mail server supports `SMTPUTF8`, the configuration will be invalid. The UTF-8 contents(such as Chinese) in `Subject`、`Attachments file name`, will be sent directly in the form of `UTF-8 encoding` pure text, `Base64` transcoding will not be performed. The synchronization method (`Send`) is not affected by this.

Specific details refer to questions：[https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/problem/381046/smtpclient%E4%B8%80%E5%A4%84%E4%BB%A3%E7%A0%81%E7%BC%96%E5%86%99%E9%94%99%E8%AF%AF%E5%AF%BC%E8%87%B4%E5%BC%82%E6%AD%A5%E5%8F%91%E9%80%81%E9%82%AE%E4%BB%B6%E6%97%B6deliveryformat%E9%85%8D%E7%BD%AE%E9%A1%B9%E6%97%A0%E6%B3%95%E6%AD%A3%E7%A1%AE%E5%B7%A5%E4%BD%9C.html](https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/problem/381046/smtpclient%E4%B8%80%E5%A4%84%E4%BB%A3%E7%A0%81%E7%BC%96%E5%86%99%E9%94%99%E8%AF%AF%E5%AF%BC%E8%87%B4%E5%BC%82%E6%AD%A5%E5%8F%91%E9%80%81%E9%82%AE%E4%BB%B6%E6%97%B6deliveryformat%E9%85%8D%E7%BD%AE%E9%A1%B9%E6%97%A0%E6%B3%95%E6%AD%A3%E7%A1%AE%E5%B7%A5%E4%BD%9C.html)

## Reappear code

Note：I use .NET Framework 4.5 to test the code, Because the affected part of the .NET Framework is consistent with .NET Core and does not affect replication, but I did not test .NET Core.
``` C#
var yourOutlookMailAddr = "xiangyuecn@outlook.com";//This is changed to your outlook mailbox. Outlook supports SMTPUTF8.

var msg = new MailMessage("test@localhost", yourOutlookMailAddr);
msg.HeadersEncoding = msg.BodyEncoding = msg.SubjectEncoding = Encoding.UTF8;

var smtp = new SmtpClient("outlook-com.olc.protection.outlook.com", 25);
smtp.DeliveryFormat = SmtpDeliveryFormat.SevenBit;

try {
	//Affected transmission mode
	msg.Subject = "SendMailAsync 中文 Test 测试";
	var task = smtp.SendMailAsync(msg);
	task.Wait();
	Console.WriteLine("SendMailAsync OK");

	//Unaffected mode of transmission
	msg.Subject = "Send 中文 Test 测试";
	smtp.Send(msg);
	Console.WriteLine("Send OK");
} catch (AggregateException e) {
	Console.WriteLine("Send Fail：");
	Console.WriteLine(e.InnerException.ToString());
}
Console.ReadLine();
```

### inspect
You can use Wireshark to find that the `Subject Header` content sent by `SendMailAsync` is not encoded at all. The Base64 code is sent by the `Send` method.

In addition, you can go to the outlook mailbox (** garbage box **) to check the source of the mail, and you will find it:

