```

## Causes and Solutions

The root cause is that in the `SmtpClient.SendMailCallback` method the `message.BeginSend` `allowUnicode` parameter is passed directly into `ServerSupportsEai`, instead of a unified `IsUnicodeSupported()`.
```
// src/System.Net.Mail/src/System/Net/Mail/SmtpClient.cs

private void SendMailCallback(IAsyncResult result)
	...
	_message.BeginSend(_writer, DeliveryMethod != SmtpDeliveryMethod.Network,
                        ServerSupportsEai, new AsyncCallback(SendMessageCallback), result.AsyncState);
	...
}
```

Change `ServerSupportsEai` to `IsUnicodeSupported()` problem solving.
```
// src/System.Net.Mail/src/System/Net/Mail/SmtpClient.cs

private void SendMailCallback(IAsyncResult result)
	...
	_message.BeginSend(_writer, DeliveryMethod != SmtpDeliveryMethod.Network,
                        IsUnicodeSupported(), new AsyncCallback(SendMessageCallback), result.AsyncState);
	...
}
```


