When reading the .NET Framework assembly `System.EnterpriseServices.Wrapper.dll` (attached) with `System.Reflection.Metadata.MetadataReader`, the `IsAssembly` property returns false.

This behavior can easily be reproduced:

```cs
static void Main(string[] args)
{
  string filePath = "System.EnterpriseServices.Wrapper.dll";
  var peReader = new PEReader(File.OpenRead(filePath));
  var metadataReader = peReader.GetMetadataReader();
  if (!metadataReader.IsAssembly)
  {
    throw new Exception($"{filePath} is not an assembly!");
  }

}
```

